      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: use active vision model for image tool fallback",
        "body": "## Root cause\nThe `image` tool only treated `agents.defaults.imageModel` or auto/default media candidates as usable image-capable models. When `agents.defaults.imageModel` was empty, a run whose active model already supported image input could still fail with `No image model is configured` instead of using that active model for explicit image-tool analysis.\n\n## Fix\n- Pass the active reply model metadata into `createImageTool`.\n- Let image-tool model resolution consider that active model first when it supports image input.\n- Preserve explicit `agents.defaults.imageModel`, fallback ordering, provider auth checks, and provider/model ref normalization.\n\n## Verification\n- `PATH=/opt/homebrew/opt/node@22/bin:$PATH pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/openclaw-tools.ts src/agents/tools/image-tool.ts src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.tts-config.test.ts`\n- `PATH=/opt/homebrew/opt/node@22/bin:$PATH node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.tts-config.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n\n## Coverage\nThe regression test now focuses on the broken path: an attachment/local image with a vision-capable active model and no `agents.defaults.imageModel`. Existing image-tool tests continue covering data URLs, remote media, schema, sandboxing, provider fallbacks, and explicit image model behavior.\n\n## Live proof\n- Local mock provider run with `agents.defaults.imageModel` unset and active model `openai/gpt-5.5`.\n- `createImageTool` executed against a real local image and selected `openai/gpt-5.5`.\n- Output: `mock-ok openai/gpt-5.5`\n- Details: `model: openai/gpt-5.5`, `image: /var/folders/.../workspace/photo.png`, `attempts: []`\n",
